description: A classic wood used the world over, Teak internal doors aren’t popular for no reason. Suitable for contemporary or traditional homes, it is a more neutral wood that suits a range of interior decors and is perfect for offices or homes.

description: The term Olive Ash does not refer to any specific species of Ash (Fraxinus genus) but instead is in reference to the darker, streaked heartwood found in some Ash trees, which tends to resemble the wood of Olive trees in the Olea genus. And it should come as little surprise that Olive Ash can be a dead ringer for actual Olive.
name: Olive Ash

description: Reddish brown sometimes with darker streaks present, it has a fine to medium straight grain with a good lustre. The resin from the bark is sometimes used as perfume. Etimoe has one of the best strength to weight ratios of any wood in the world.
